<TITLE> PIO unit boost planned to curb police graft: Sahara </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com)Home minister Sahara Khatun on Monday told the parliament that the Police Internal Oversight (PIO) unit activities would be made more dynamic to curb corruption by the key law-enforcing agency. In a written speech addressing a slew of questions, the home minister elaborated that the PIO was formed to ensure the police did not get entangled in bribery, corruption and immoral activities. Questioned by Noakhali-6 MP Fazlul Azim, Khatun said as per government directives, senior police officers have initiated strict measures to monitor and make sure the policemen keep themselves away from corrupt practices. Replying to Syeda Ashifa Ashrafee Papia, MP's query, the minister said the 2001-2006 BNP-led coalition government had recruited 1,475 sub-inspectors, 268 sergeants and 32, 499 constables. Industrial police force The minister while answering Chittagong-11 MP Shamsul Haque Chowdhury's question said that the government took steps to raise an industrial police contingent comprising 1, 580 policemen, which may be further expanded. Illegal immigrants Questioned by Cox's Bazaar-3 MP Lutfar Rahman, she said an estimated 2, 85, 329 illegal immigrants have encroached upon Bangladesh territories, most of who are the Rohingiya from Myanmar. Law and order Responding to a query by Jafrul Islam Chowdhury, MP from Chittagong-15, the home minister said the overall security situation was under control. The law-enforcement agencies have been directed to ensure public safety and take strictest legal measures against any defaulters, she adsed
